==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stockdove
<hw>Stock"dove`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A common European wild pigeon (<spn>Columba aenas</spn>), so called
because at one time believed to be the stock of the domestic pigeon, or,
according to some, from its breeding in the stocks, or trunks, of
trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is applied, also, to other related species, as
the Indian <xex>stockdove</xex> (<spn>Palumbaena
Eversmanni</spn>).</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stocker</ent>⟦br⟧
